# Ship Day - Research -> Store -> Show
#
# These are set as Codespaces secrets, NOT in this file.
# Go to https://github.com/settings/codespaces -> New secret,
# grant each one Repository access to your assignment repo,
# then restart your Codespace so they load.
#
# This file documents the names only. Never paste real values here --
# it is committed to your repo.
#
# Check them from your Codespace terminal with:
#   echo $TAVILY_API_KEY
# A blank line means the secret is missing, misnamed, has no repository
# access, or your Codespace needs restarting.

# ---- Part 1 ----
# Tavily: web search for your agent. Starts with tvly-
# tavily.com -> sign up -> copy the API key from the dashboard
# Free tier: 1,000 searches/month, no credit card.
TAVILY_API_KEY=

# ---- Part 2 ----
# Netlify: personal access token. Deploys your site.
# Treat it like a password -- it can deploy to any site on your account.
# app.netlify.com -> avatar -> User settings -> Applications ->
#   Personal access tokens -> New access token
# Netlify shows it once. Lost it? Delete it and make another.
NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=

# ---- Part 4 ----
# Netlify: which project to deploy to. You get this by creating your
# project from the command line:
#   npm install -g netlify-cli
#   netlify sites:create --name YOURNAME-shipday
# Copy the "Site ID" from the output.
#
# Not secret, but stored the same way so your scripts read all three
# values identically -- and so deploys never stop to ask you questions.
NETLIFY_SITE_ID=

# No database credentials here on purpose. Your results live in a plain
# file in your Codespace -- a JSON file or a SQLite database. Ask your
# agent which it picked and why; you need that for your delegation log.
#
# Whatever you put in public/ is on the internet. Keep your data file
# and scripts out of it.
